   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_196288_1826-04_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <date when="1826-04-22">April 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1826</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                            My dead <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrewD1">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Brewster</persName>
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               <quote>"Take up your pen"</quote> --<lb/>
               <quote>"My dear Madam It is<lb/>
                        in my hand already"</quote> --<lb/>
                    -- <quote>"I am glad of it</quote> -- then<lb/>
                    never lay it down again till<lb/>
                    you have answered this<lb/>
                    question -- which you may<lb/>
                    do in two minutes &amp; in<lb/>
                    a note of two lines --<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>  Will you or will you not<lb/>
                    come to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
               <lb/>
                    this summer? --<lb/>
                    I must write to <persName ref="./Placeography.xml#HersX1">Herschel</persName>
               <lb/>
                    &amp; you must empower me<lb/>
                    to say <hi rend="underline">yes</hi> - before he sets out<lb/>
                    on his tour or makes his<lb/>
                    final arrangements --<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>  When I say will you come<lb/>
                    to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName> of course<lb/>
                    you understand I mean <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrewM1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>.<lb/>
                        Brewster</persName> &amp; all of yours you can<lb/>
                    bring <lb/>
            </p>
            <note place="top">Do not<lb/>
                    make<lb/>
                    good the<lb/>
                    sad old<lb/>
                    proverb<lb/>
               <quote>"No stars<lb/>
                    shine for<lb/>
                        Irishmen"</quote>
               <lb/>
            </note>
            <closer>
                    Ever y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. obliged &amp; grateful<lb/>
                    direct <hi rend="underline">thro</hi>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParsL1">Earl of Rosse</persName> - <placeName ref="Parsonstown-House_IE">Parsons Town</placeName> as usual<lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p/>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
               </address>
            </closer>
